Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are an acceptable approach to solving the serious problems of SOFC technology, such as sealing and mechanical strength.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, commercial stainless-steel plates, STS430, are used as supporting bodies for a metal-supported SOFC in order to decrease the number of fabrication steps.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The metal support for a single-cell has a diameter of 28 mm, a thickness of 1 mm, and a channel width of 0.4 mm.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A thin ceramic layer, composed of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) and NiO/YSZ, is attached to the metal support by using a cermet adhesive.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Co0.4Mn0.6O3 perovskite oxide serves as the cathode material because of its low impedance on the YSZ electrolyte, according to half-cell tests.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell is 0.09 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of temperature, oxygen partial pressure, and current collection by pastes are investigated.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction at the cathode dominates the overall cell performance, according to experimental and numerical analyses.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
